author: The Virginian-Pilot
title: Thursday's roundup | Western Branch hands Bishop Sullivan 1st loss
text:
BOYS VOLLEYBALL Western Branch 3, Bishop Sullivan 1
Antonio Sargent tallied 15 kills, Chris Cox had 32 assists and the Bruins handed the No. 8 Crusaders their first loss on Thursday.
Bishop Sullivan (20-1) won the first set 25-16 before the Bruins took the next three 25-16, 25-16, 25-19.
"Tonight we served tough and we put balls away," Western Branch coach Jason Parker said.
Chad Heidelberger added 10 kills and Matt Rudisill had 11 digs for the Bruins (12-7).
Bishop Sullivan, enjoying its best season in the four-team Tidewater Conference, won three of their previous four matches in five sets to keep their unbeaten streak intact.
Bayside 3, Kellam 1
Max Ebert paced the top-ranked Marlins (14-5, 9-1 Coastal) in a 25-20, 25-18, 23-25, 25-18 victory.
Bayside's Michael King had nine kills and Sean Davidson chipped in 32 assists.
Maury 3, Green Run 0
Andrew Lyons and James Whitham combined for eight kills, Charlie Seerden added 32 assists and the fourth-ranked Commodores (18-6, 5-0 Atlantic) swept the Stallions 25-9, 25-13, 25-15. Maury's Ashlar Peronnet had five kills.
Landstown 3, Tallwood 0
Christian Brown delivered 23 assists and Tripp McGuire had 11 kills as the No. 10 Eagles (8-9, 5-5 Coastal) swept the Lions 25-20, 25-19, 25-14.
Derek Evans had eight kills for Landstown.
GIRLS VOLLEYBALL
Ocean Lakes 3, First Colonial 0
Taylor Allbritten and Liv Crawley combined for 30 kills as the No. 2 Dolphins swept the No. 4 Patriots 25-23, 25-19, 25-23.
Alisi Motu'apuaka had 38 assists and four aces for the Dolphins (16-4, 9-2), who were coming off a five-set loss to No. 1 Kellam on Tuesday.
Coach Jack Wheeler helped make sure his team had no hangover against another elite Coastal Conference rival.
"We were trying to focus on things we needed to get better at," Wheeler said.
Norfolk Christian 3, Peninsula Catholic 2
Sam Verhaagen amassed 71 digs, Natalie Marshall had 21 kills and the Ambassadors (18-6, 7-1) topped the Trojans in a key Tidewater Conference match-up 19-25, 23-25, 25-20, 25-18, 18-16.
Lake Taylor 3, Wilson 2
Britney Weaver tallied 11 kills and the Titans survived 25-17, 18-25, 25-27, 25-21, 15-9.
In the fifth set, Jazmyn Doster had five service points and three kills.
Lakeland 3, Denbigh 1
Makayla Byrum and DeMari Turner had six kills apiece, Kayla Barnes had five kills and the Cavaliers won 25-13, 20-25, 25-23, 25-22.
Granby 3, Woodside 1
Hannah Talliere paced the No. 9 Comets with 18 kills in a Monitor-Merrimac Conference win.
Princess Anne 3, Salem 0
Abby Bottomley and Ashley Burgess totaled 18 kills, Alyssa Presto supplied 28 assists and the No. 3 Cavaliers (20-2, 5-0 Atlantic) cruised.
